OL,6,     FThe next leg of his trip sees
OL,7,     FJames heading to Bresse, home of
OL,8,     Fone of the country's most famous
OL,9,     Fingredients - the Bresse chicken.
OL,10,     FHe visits a chicken farm to
OL,11,     Fdiscover just why these birds are
OL,12,     Fso special, and gets the chance to
OL,13,     Fcook his own. He also meets
OL,14,     FGeorges Blanc, one of his culinary
OL,15,     Fheroes, before attending the
OL,16,     Fannual Michelin star football
OL,17,     Ftournament
